The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 14: The government will rope in private players to revive 18 National Textile Corporation (NTC) mills through the joint venture route. ?A public notice inviting private players for joint venture to revive the mills will be issued in the first week of September,? sources said. A total of 40 NTC mills will be revived, of which the government will take the sole responsibility for 22.

 New Delhi, Aug. 14: The government is in favour of raising the monthly contribution to the EPFO?s pension scheme. It also wants to increase the eligibility age for receiving pension from 58 to 60 years to reduce its future liabilities.

 New Delhi, Aug. 14: The government can raise Rs 31,000 crore in the current stock market boom by divesting only 10 per cent of its stake in each of the top 14 public sector undertakings, according to an estimate by Assocham.

 Mumbai, Aug. 14: Sharekhan is looking at various options, including an initial public offering, to raise capital to fund its expansion plans, director Jaideep Arora said.

 New Delhi, Aug. 14: Sundaram Mutual aims to mop up more than Rs 300 crore from its new Capex Opportunities Fund, which will invest mostly in equity of capital goods companies to generate consistent long-term returns.




